The sexism of the television industry, in 6 charts
's Olivia Pope and  's Alicia Florrick may be front and center in many TV fans' hearts, but women are still highly underrepresented in the television industry. According to a new study,  , women's roles both on screen and behind the scenes have declined in the past few years.  was conducted by the Center for the Study of Women in Television and Film at San Diego State University and randomly selects one episode to use as analysis.  The report analysis studies broadcast network television and cable television, and Netflix, so yes   is included. For all forms of television combined, the report found that women comprised only 40 percent of speaking roles on the screen. Behind the scenes, women only comprised 25 percent of individuals in key roles. Here are some of those roles broken down:   
   
   
     
     
     
       
